## Loaded first. Control directives.
## Delete all existing rules.
-D
## Kernel backlog buffer — 'log everything' needs headroom. Raise if auditctl -s shows lost>0.
-b 16384
## Failure mode: 1=printk (log). Never 2=panic on a workstation.
-f 1
## Drop events instead of throttling the whole system under flood.
--backlog_wait_time 0
## Ignore load errors (e.g. a syscall not present on this arch).
-i
